romide, Phenampromide, Propiram.\n13. Benzimidazoles — including Clonitazene, Etonitazene, Bezitramide.\n14. Phencyclidine (PCP) (1-(1-phenylcyclohexyl)piperidine), its salts, derivatives and analogues — including Ketamine (2-(2-chlorophenyl)-2-(methylamino)cyclohexanone).\n15. Piritramide.\n16. Fentanyls, their salts, derivatives, and analogues — including Acetyl-alpha-methylfentanyl, Alfentanil, Carfentanil, p-Fluorofentanyl, Fentanyl, beta-Hydroxyfentanyl, alpha-Methylfentanyl, 3-Methylfentanyl, Remifentanil, Sufentanil, Thiofentanyl, and 4-Anilino-N-phenethylpiperidine (ANPP).\n17. Tilidine.\n17.1 Methylenedioxypyrovalerone (MDPV), its salts, derivatives, isomers and analogues.\n18. Methamphetamine (N,alpha-dimethylbenzeneethanamine), its salts, derivatives, isomers and analogues.\n19. Amphetamines, their salts, derivatives, isomers and analogues — including amphetamine, N-ethylamphetamine, STP (DOM), MDA (3,4-methylenedioxyamphetamine), 4-methoxyamphetamine, MDMA-related N-methyl-3,4-methylenedioxyamphetamine, DOET, 4-bromo-2,5-dimethoxyamphetamine, Benzphetamine, 3,4,5-trimethoxyamphetamine.\n20. Flunitrazepam (Rohypnol) and any of its salts or derivatives.\n21. 4-hydroxybutanoic acid (GHB) and any of its salts.\n22. Tapentadol, its salts, derivatives and isomers.\n23. AH-7921, its salts, isomers and salts of isomers.\n24. MT-45, its salts, derivatives, isomers and analogues — including Diphenidine (DEP), Methoxphenidine (MXP), Ephenidine, Isophenidine — but not including Lefetamine.\n25. W-18, its salts, derivatives, isomers and analogues.\n26. U-47700, its salts, derivatives, isomers and analogues — including Bromadoline, U-47109, U-48520, U-50211, U-77891.\n27. Tramadol, its salts, isomers and salts of isomers, and the derivatives O-desmethyltramadol and N,O-didesmethyltramadol.\n28. AP-237 (1-(4-cinnamylpiperazin-1-yl)butan-1-one), its salts, derivatives and analogues — including 2-methyl-AP-237, para-methyl-AP-237, AP-238.",
